Russian Equity Movers: Dixy Group, Gazprom Neft, Razgulay

-- B y   J a s o n   C o r c o r a n
-- 
2011-09-05T15:26:22Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-05/russian-equity-movers-gazprom-neft-razgulay-shares-are-active.html
The 30-stock  Micex Index (INDEXCF)  fell for a
second day, losing 1.5 percent to 1,492.83 by the 6:45 p.m.
close in Moscow. The dollar-denominated RTS Index dropped 2.4
percent to 1,617.01.  The following were among the most active stocks in the
Russian market today. Stock symbols are in parenthesis.  OAO Dixy Group (DIXY RX), a Russian supermarket chain, rose
for the fifth day in the past six after reporting a 23 percent
increase in seven-month sales to 44.1 billion rubles ($1.5
billion) from a year earlier. The stock gained 1.6 percent to
291.64 rubles.  OAO Gazprom Neft (SIBN RX), the oil arm of Russiaâ€™s gas
monopoly, fell the most in more than two weeks after crude slid
below $84 a barrel in  New York . The stock lost 2.7 percent to
123.87 rubles, its worst drop since Aug. 19.  OAO  Razgulay Group (GRAZ)  , a Russian sugar producer,
retreated its most in more than two weeks as white sugar fell in
 London . The stock slipped as much as 4.2 percent before closing
2.1 percent lower at 36.77 rubles, its biggest fall since Aug.
